Name: biotinidase deficiency
Definition: A multiple carboxylase deficiency that involves a deficiency in biotinidase.

Name: obsolete carcinoma in situ of breast and genitourinary system
Definition: A multiple carboxylase deficiency that involves a deficiency in biotinidase.
Synonym: carcinoma in situ of breast and genitourinary system (disorder)

Name: holocarboxylase synthetase deficiency
Definition: A multiple carboxylase deficiency that involves a deficiency in holocarboxylase synthetase.
